<CSSMin-width>
<summary>
The <strong><c>min-width</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> property sets the minimum width of an element. It prevents the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/used_value">used value</see> of the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/width">width</see> property from becoming smaller than the value specified for <c>min-width</c>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/min-width.html")</para><para>The element&amp;apos;s width is set to the value of <c>min-width</c> whenever <c>min-width</c> is larger than <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/max-width">max-width</see> or <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/width">width</see>.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/width">width</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/max-width">max-width</see><br/>-The <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_box_model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model">box model</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-sizing">box-sizing</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/min-width"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</CSSMin-width>
